This paper is about sentiment analysis, which is a subfield of natural language processing (NLP) and falls under the category of computational linguistics (cs.CL). The paper proposes a new method for sentiment analysis that utilizes deep neural networks, which is a popular technique in artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and machine learning (cs.LG). The paper also discusses data augmentation techniques, which are commonly used in information retrieval (cs.IR) and data mining (cs.SI). Therefore, the most likely sub-categories are cs.CL, cs.AI, and cs.LG, followed by cs.IR and cs.SI.
